news.title: Noida authority's CEO to meet all stakeholders for roadmap to raze Supertech twin towers
news.para: The meeting will be attended by officials from the district administration, police, discom PVVNL, Gas Authority of India Ltd (GAIL), the state pollution control board, the controller of explosives, Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) and the RWAs of both Emerald Court and ATS Greens Village, which is the immediate neighbour of the twin towers.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC asked for refund plan for Green View homebuyers
news.para: Gurgaon’s outgoing deputy commissioner Yash Garg directed NBCC to come back with a concrete proposal regarding repairs or refund of money to the homebuyers before initiating any action for eviction.

news.title: SC asks AG to submit guidelines to regulate land allotment to housing societies
news.para: A bench comprising Chief Justice N V Ramana and Justices A S Bopanna and Hima Kohli said that now the scope of the petition has been expanded, the plea may be listed after the AG submits guidelines, proposed by him, to govern the allotment of land to housing societies nationwide.

news.title: Sebi to auction seven properties of Saradha Realty on February 22
news.para: Inviting bids for sale of properties in the recovery proceedings against Saradha Realty and its promoters/ directors, Sebi said the e-auction will take place on February 22, 2022.

news.title: UK housing boom starts to fade as cost-of-living squeeze tightens: Halifax
news.para: Russell Galley, managing director at Halifax, said "it remains likely that the rate of house price growth will slow considerably over the next year" even as the limited supply of houses for sale will provide some support to prices.

news.title: DVAC probing land transfer in Tiruttani area for astronomical sum
news.para: Assuming the value of the real estate is so much, it would have entailed payment of at least 62,000 crore towards stamp fee and registration charges alone.

news.title: Drone & DGPS surveys set to begin in select areas of Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: ​While Vizhinjam, Mulloor, Kottapuram and Venganoor have been selected as the areas for the preparation of TPS, the Palayam, Thampanoor, Vazhuthacaud and Thycaud wards have been selected for the preparation of the LAP in the city.

news.title: Madras HC seeks details of illegal construction at ASI heritage site
news.para: Admitting the plea on Monday, the first bench of Chief Justice Munishwar Nath Bhandari and D Bharatha Charkravarthy directed the special government pleader to find out the actual distance between the new construction and the monument by February 11.

news.title: DLF phase 1-3 residents await infra work & takeover by Gurugram civic body
news.para: MCG officials said the deadline was over on December 31 last year, but the developer has not yet started work on internal roads. The civic body will now submit a report to the state government on the status of the takeover of the three private colonies.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body starts digitising property tax files
news.para: Out of around 1.20 lakh files of both residential and commercial properties, over 15,000 are already digitised. Not only documents, details of taxes paid and arrears, will be maintained digitally by the tax branch of the civic body.

news.title: Interest subsidy of Rs 41,415 crore disbursed so far under PMAY-Urban: Government
news.para: Union Housing and Urban Affairs Minister Hardeep Singh Puri said subsidy of Rs 5,320 crore has been disbursed so far under the Credit Linked Subsidy Scheme (CLSS) in the current financial year.

news.title: DDA extends last date to apply for special housing scheme
news.para: The new special housing scheme offers a little over 18,000 flats, with all units being drawn from its old inventory. The last date of the scheme was February 7, 2022, when it was announced.

news.title: GNIDA to impose Rs 10 lakh fine on unauthorised use of authority logo
news.para: Any companies or builders found using the GNIDA logo without permission will be charged a fine of Rs 10 lakh followed by cancellation lease deed.

news.title: Livspace turns unicorn with $180 million KKR-led funding
news.para: The home renovation platform is the 86th "unicorn" from India, according to Venture Intelligence Unicorn Tracker, in a period of record funding in Indian start-ups that saw 43 firms join the club last year alone.

news.title: Aurum PropTech to acquire 53% stake in Grexter Housing Solutions for Rs 27 crore
news.para: Grexter Living will be utilising this growth capital to scale up its business in co-living space. It is aiming to strengthen product offering by improving its technology platform and focusing on community-led engagement in its co-living spaces.
